=m><span class=title> The Interface</span><hr size=1> I played NWN for a couple of hours last night. I think it's pretty cool. <br>
<br>
I love the interface. Im a big Keyboard shortcut freak, so its pretty good in that regard, and I haven't fully explored it.<br>
The right-click &quot;radial&quot; menu is cool, plus you can use the NumPad keys to select the same selections as the &quot;radial&quot; menu.<br>
<br>
Its much cleaner and easier to use than previous D&amp;D games. They let you use up to 36 slots for shortcuts, and customizing them is no sweat.<br>
<br>
I only have 1 minor gripe. I really wish that they would make keyboard shortcuts for the Inventory screen. The little tab buttons on the right side are good idea instead of scrolling around BUT it gets tedious trying to select them. The buttons are very small. I like to keep diff types of items in diff tabs, so organization gets a little slow during this. <br>
<br>
They should make the Tabs numbered to the Non NumPad number keys, that way you can switch quickly. or use the actual &quot;tab&quot; key to switch between them.<br>
<br>
That's my 2 cents.<br>
